<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rexrodt, Iran's Velayati Discuss Economic Ties </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rexrodt, Iran's Velayati Discuss Economic Ties </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1406123494 Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network in German 1100 
GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1406123494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cologne Deutschlandfunk Network </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Federal Economics Minister Guenther Rexrodt has 
called on Iran to continue promptly settling the claims of 
German creditors. It will only make sense to consider holding 
another meeting of the German-Iranian Economic Commission once 
the debt rescheduling agreement that was concluded in February 
has been fulfilled, Rexrodt said at a meeting with Foreign 
Minister Velayati in Bonn. 
  According to official information, Rexrodt and Velayati 
agree 
that both sides are interested in the further development of 
economic relations. 

</TEXT>

