<H3> <TI>   Progress in EU Trade Negotiations With Lithuania Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Progress in EU Trade Negotiations With Lithuania Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1006121794 London REUTER Textline Database in English 9 
Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1006121794 </F>
<F P=104>  London REUTER Textline Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article from Brussels EUROPE: "Free-Trade </F>
Agreement With Lithuania Should Be Initialled Before End of 
Month"] 
  [Text] The third round of negotiations with a view to 
concluding a EU/Lithuania free-trade agreement led to 
"substantial progress" between the Community delegation (led by 
Mr. Guggenbuhl of DGI) and the Lithuanian delegation led by Mr. 
Grybauskaite of the Foreign Ministry. So much so that the 
agreement could probably be initialled before the end of the 
month. Defined, notably, were: the text of the draft agreement, 
the list of industrial products for which Lithuania will benefit 
from a period of transition, the provisions on textiles, 
processed agricultural products, customs cooperation and rules 
of origin. Moreover, the positions aligned more as to the 
reciprocal concessions for agricultural products and fishing, 
said a note from the Commission. 

</TEXT>

