<H3> <TI>   CSU Leaders Call Euroelections `Vote for Kohl' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSU Leaders Call Euroelections `Vote for Kohl' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1306094194 Hamburg DPA in German 0838 GMT 13 Jun 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1306094194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Munich (DPA) -- The Christian Social Union [CSU] 
leadership assessed the election to the European Parliament in 
Germany as a "vote for Kohl." Before the beginning of the 
executive committee session of his party in Munich on Monday [13 
June], CSU Chairman Theo Waigel said that Social Democratic 
Party of Germany [SPD] challenger Rudolf Scharping had made the 
mistake of underestimating the chancellor. "Scharping does not 
look so good, this is an open secret." 
  Bavarian Minister President Edmund Stoiber said: "It was 
certainly a vote for Kohl. The SPD has to decide whether it was 
also an anti-Scharping vote." 
  After the CSU's surprisingly good performance, Waigel called 
on his own party immediately to start the work for the Landtag 
and Bundestag elections in the fall. "We are not arrogant now." 
Bavaria's SPD, with its chairwoman Renate Schmidt, has been 
dampened. Schmidt does not have an answer to questions of the 
future and she is trying to divert the people's attention from 
it with cheap propaganda tricks, it was stated. 

</TEXT>

