<F P=103> AU1306114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Berlin (DPA) -- Gregor Gysi, chairman of the Party 
of Democratic Socialism [PDS] Bundestag Group, is confident that 
his party will have the strength of a parliamentary group in the 
next Bundestag. It is very likely that it will not be possible 
to prevent the PDS from entering the Bundestag again, Gysi told 
DPA on Monday [13 June]. 
  After the very good performance in the municipal elections 
in 
the east and the European elections, Gysi stated that the PDS 
will at least get three direct mandates, "but it might also be 
five to 10." The 5-percent hurdle can also be overcome. In 
Gysi's opinion, the Social Democratic Party of Germany [SPD] 
still has not been able to gain a foothold in the new laender. 
It does not have any relation to reality and to history in the 
east. 

