<H3> <TI>   Treasury Notes Decreased Need for Deficit Financing </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Treasury Notes Decreased Need for Deficit Financing </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1006125894 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1413 GMT 9 
Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1006125894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Public Sector Borrowing Requirement </F>
Declines in First Quarter"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, June 9 -- Italy's public sector 
borrowing requirement [PSBR] declined by 18 percent in the first 
quarter of the year against the same quarter in 1993, the 
Treasury reported today and said the figure came to 42.399 
trillion lire (26.23 billion dollars), a quarterly PSBR nine 
trillion below the 51.657 trillion disclosed at the end of March 
last year. 
  Over the first three months of the year, spending came to 
132.032 trillion lire (81.7 billion dollars) against revenues of 
101.715 trillion lire leaving a net balance of 30.317 trillion 
to finance, plus 12.071 trillion lire generated by Treasury 
management operations. 
  The release of these figures today boosted cautious optimism 
on the prospect of lowering the PSBR also over the longer term. 
Yesterday, the studies center of the national manufacturers 
association, Confindustria [General Confederation of Italian 
Industry], estimated PSBR for the first five months of the year 
at 75.4 trillion lire (46.66 billion dollars), against 87,800 
trillion lire (54.33 billion dollars) for the same period in 
1993, but would not dismiss worries about exceeding the PSBR 
forecast for the full year. 
  The forecast deficit for 1994 drafted by the government led 
by Premier Carlo Azeglio Ciampi is 159 trillion lire (98.39 
billion dollars) and this figure has been spoken of as reliable 
by the new economic team installed by Premier Silvio Berlusconi. 
  If the trend reported for the first quarter continues as is, 
the PSBR would come to 169.552 trillion lire by December 31, 
more than 10.5 trillion lire over target, but Treasury 
technicians said account must be taken of the range of variables 
on both the spending and revenues sides which condition budget 
management. Among the factors conditioning the figures for the 
first quarter were the virtual paralysis of public investments 
and the reduction of debt servicing thanks to falling interest 
rates. 
  Even taking these variables into consideration, said the 
Confindustria studies center, "rigorous conduct on the side of 
the public administration" could lead to a deficit for the full 
year of 152 to 154 trillion lire. 

</TEXT>

