<H3> <TI>   Rwandan RPF Thanks Government, Requests More Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rwandan RPF Thanks Government, Requests More Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0906104094 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 1900 GMT 8 
Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0906104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Rwanda/Italy: Refugees Receive </F>
Hospital Treatment, RPF Representative in Rome"] 
  [Excerpt] (ANSA) Rome, June 8 -- A representative of the 
Rwandan Popular Front (RPF) flew into Rome Wednesday [8 June] to 
thank the Italian Government for bringing out 93 severely 
wounded refugees, and to urge further aid for his country. 
  The representative of the opposition group, Jacques 
Bihozagara, was met at the airport by Maria Pia Fanfani, 
president of the Insieme per la Pace (Together for Peace) 
organisation which managed to get the refugees, which included 
75 orphaned children and the Rwandan national soccer team, out 
of the war-torn country. 
  Bihozagara said he was in Rome "to thank the Italian 
Government and people, which have already done so much for 
Rwanda, but also to explain the situation in my country, and the 
need to get medicines, healthcare aid and food as soon as 
possible." 
  Fanfani said that her organisation was working with the 
Italian Government on plans to send aid ships to Rwanda. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

