<H3> <TI>   DPRK Minister Stops in Berlin for `Technical Reasons' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    DPRK Minister Stops in Berlin for `Technical Reasons' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1006140294 Hamburg DPA in German 1311 GMT 10 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1006140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- North Korean Foreign Minister Kim 
Yong- nam stopped over in Berlin on his flight from Kiev to 
Pyongyang. On Friday [10 June], the Foreign Ministry in Bonn 
said the minister arrived on Thursday night and would continue 
his trip on Friday night. He had not asked for any talks and 
there were no plans for talks either. It was said that it was a 
transit stop for "technical" reasons. 
  The North Korean had visited the Ukrainian capital before. 
He was actually scheduled to go to one of the central Asian 
republics but changed his plans at short notice. His flight 
back to Pyongyang went through Berlin. 

</TEXT>

