<F P=106> [Unattributed article from Brussels EUROPE: "King Hassan </F>
Hosts EU'S Van den Broek"] 
  [Text] King Hassan II of Morocco has received European 
Commissioner for External Relations Hans Van den Broek. The 
prospect of a new EU/Morocco agreement and the role of Morocco 
in the Mediterranean region were discussed. Mr. van den Broek 
said at the close of the meeting that Morocco was a pole of 
stability and a peace factor in his region. Regarding the 
agreement envisaged, he said that, for some aspects, there was 
already a broad basis of consensus, but that others seemed to be 
more difficult. EUROPE recalls that Morocco has submitted 
counter-proposals to the content of the new agreement, and that, 
before the opening of official negotiations, preparatory 
discussions are to be continued. 

