<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlusconi Begins Official Visit 16 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Berlusconi Begins Official Visit 16 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Highlights Joint Economic Interests </H4>

<F P=102> LD1506193794 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1854 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- A day before his visit to Bonn, 
Italian Government head Silvio Berlusconi has highlighted the 
joint economic interests of both countries. Italy was one of 
the first countries to be interested in a commitment to Eastern 
Germany, Berlusconi said in an interview in the Bonn daily 
GENERAL-ANZEIGER (Thursday's [16 June] edition). 
  His country is now one of the leading investors in the East 
German states. Over 40 Italian companies have already 
established themselves on the territory of the former GDR. This 
represented "a major flow of investment," which has also led to 
the creation of new jobs, the prime minister said. 
  Berlusconi defended the cooperation between his party and 
the 
neofascists of the National Alliance. This could not be 
compared with the right-wing extremist French Front National or 
the Republicans in Germany. 

</TEXT>

