<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   CDU Wins in Thuringia Elections </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CDU Wins in Thuringia Elections </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506172194 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1628 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506172194 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Erfurt, (DDP/ADN) -- The provisional final 
results of the Thuringian district and town council elections 
reveal that the CDU [Christian Democratic Union] has gained 37.1 
percent of the votes -- 4.8 percent less than in the 1990 local 
elections. The regional returning officer said today in Erfurt 
that the SPD [Social Democratic Party] has gained 26.1 percent, 
6.5 percent more than four years ago. 
  The third largest vote went to the PDS [Party of Democratic 
Socialism], which improved its result from 5.2 percent to 15.7 
percent. The Greens sustained slight losses with 6.4 percent 
(1990: 6.6 percent). The FDP [Free Democratic Party], which 
achieved 7.7 percent in 1990, gained 6.2 percent. The DSU 
[German Social Union] dropped from 3.3 to 1.4 percent. None of 
the other parties made the 1 percent mark. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

