<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   May Send Troops </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    May Send Troops </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506190494 Paris France-2 Television Network in French 
1800 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506190494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Alain Juppe said this evening that 
if the massacres in Rwanda continue, France will send soldiers 
to Rwanda: 
  [Begin recording] [Juppe] Either the cease-fire is 
respected, 
or else the massacres go on. If they go on, then we cannot 
continue to tolerate this situation, and France would in this 
case be prepared to mount -- with others, with its European 
partners or with African states -- an operation to save the 
people. 
  [Reporter] How could such an operation be mounted? 
  [Juppe] You must surely understand that I am not going to 
spell it out for you here. France decided this morning to say 
that it is prepared to take part in such an operation, and we 
are now studying the modalities of implementation. [end 
recording] 
  Bernard Kouchner, former minister of humanitarian action, 
left for Rwanda yesterday evening. He wants to encourage 
dialogue between the different factions. 

</TEXT>

