<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Occhetto Seen as Contender for EP Presidency </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Occhetto Seen as Contender for EP Presidency </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1506143694 Rome LA REPUBBLICA in Italian 15 Jun 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> BR1506143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome LA REPUBBLICA </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Will Achille Become President in </F>
Strasbourg?"] 
  [Text] Brussels -- Will [outgoing Democratic Party of the 
Left, PDS, Secretary] Achille Occhetto become president of the 
European Parliament [EP]? In the presidential contest which has 
just started in Strasbourg, the PDS' outgoing secretary's name 
is among six leading candidates, together with the two Belgian 
former Prime Ministers Leo Tindemans and Wilfried Martens (who 
are considered the favorites), Social Democrat John Hume from 
Northern Ireland, French center-right leader Dominique Baudis, 
and Spanish millionaire Abel Matutes. The election of the 
president will take place on 19 July. Occhetto's candidacy was 
suggested by a number of left-wing exponents, as the 
standard-bearer of the European Left against "neofascism" and 
"the victory of the Right in Italy." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

