<H3> <TI>   Northern League Pledges Full Support for Government </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northern League Pledges Full Support for Government </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606082594 Rome RAI Televideo Teletext in Italian 0452 GMT 
16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606082594 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Televideo Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The first meeting of the Northern League's federal 
political secretariat ended shortly after midnight. During the 
meeting, matters pertaining to the organization and work of 
League leaders in national institutions were discussed. 
  The League confirmed its full support for the government. 
Institutional Reforms Minister Francesco Speroni also explained 
the meaning of the words laborism and independence. Laborism is 
understood as "nonconservatism" and independence as "a faction 
of constructive criticism" within the government, which 
"propels the League into goverment." 

</TEXT>

