<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hundreds Arrested in Anti-Mafia Raid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hundreds Arrested in Anti-Mafia Raid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506114994 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1100 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506114994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] There was a huge anti-Mafia operation in Milan 
this morning. Hundreds of people were arrested by the police. 
The northern gangs of the Calabrese Mafia have been broken up. 
They managed a huge drugs trade. Details of the operation were 
given a short while ago in Milan by Milan's Chief Prosecutor 
Francesco Saverio Borrelli, Chief of Police Vincenzo Parisi, and 
Interior Minister Roberto Maroni. Paola Maria Anelli reports: 
  [Anelli] [Passage omitted] Dozens of people belonging to the 
gang of Giuseppe Mazzaferro, a very important member of the 
Calabrian 'Ndrangheta, were the target of the operation. For 
many years the gang had deep roots in Lombardy, in Como, Varese, 
Milan, and Brescia. [passage omitted] A total of 370 people -- 
100 of whom were in jail -- were served with preventive 
detention warrants in Lombardy, Apulia, and Calabria. They were 
charged with holdups, extortion, drug and arms trafficking. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

