<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arms Found on Yacht in Ibiza; IRA Link Possible </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Arms Found on Yacht in Ibiza; IRA Link Possible </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506133794 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 1200 GMT 
15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506133794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The police discovered weapons and ammunition on 
board a yacht in Ibiza. This weaponry could have been destined 
for use by the Northern Ireland terrorist group, IRA. RNE in 
the Balearic Islands reports: 
  [Unidentified correspondent] Customs officers and the Civil 
Guard intercepted a consignment of weapons on a yacht moored at 
the Marina de Botafoc leisure harbor in Ibiza. Four people were 
arrested during the operation: a Briton, an Irishman, a 
Canadian, and a New Zealand woman. Among the materiel seized 
were assault rifles and machine-guns, bullet-proof vests, and 
10,000 cartridges. The police have not revealed where this 
materiel came from nor where the yacht was headed. The yacht 
had been moored at Ibiza's leisure harbor for some days. 
Initial investigations point to a possible link between the 
four arrested and the IRA terrorist organization. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

