<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Gonzalez Rules Out Early Elections, Opposes Reshuffle </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Gonzalez Rules Out Early Elections, Opposes Reshuffle </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606073194 Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network in Spanish 0700 GMT 
16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606073194 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE-1 Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Felipe Gonzalez has ruled out early general 
elections, and he does not think it is necessary to reshuffle 
his cabinet. He said this in Cartagena de Indias, Colombia, 
where the fourth Latin America summit closed last night. The 
prime minister also said that he does not think there are enough 
reasons at present to submit the goverment to a confidence vote 
in the Cortes although he would be prepared to do so were it 
necessary: 
  [Begin Gonzalez recording] I do not rule it out, but I am 
not 
giving an immediate response to that problem because it is not 
an immediate problem. [end recording] 
  In statements made before starting his journey back to 
Madrid, Gonzalez described a possible alliance with the United 
Left as difficult, but said he is open to dialogue with the 
Popular Party although with the following warning: 
  [Begin Gonzalez recording] Responsibility for government 
will 
belong to the government's under all circumstances. If the 
government cannot discharge this responsibility then it will 
have to make other decisions but what it will not to do is 
abdicate its responsibility. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

