<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Poll Shows Slight Improvement in Aho's Rating </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Poll Shows Slight Improvement in Aho's Rating </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   94P20880A Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT in Finnish 22 May 94 p 
10 </F>

<F P=103> 94P20880A </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki HELSINGIN SANOMAT </F>
<F P=105>  Finnish </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> [Finnish News Service report: "Over Half Dissatisfied With </F>
the Government"] 
  [Text] Although the government led by Prime Minister Esko 
Aho (Center Party) has increased its popular support, a majority 
53 percent of Finns are still dissatisfied with it. 
  According to an opinion poll conducted by Gallup of Finland 
for the [Oulu] newspaper KALEVA, less than one-fifth of 
citizens, or 18 percent, are satisfied with the government, and 
of these, only 2 percent said they were extremely well 
satisfied. 
  All told, the proportion of those satisfied with the 
government has risen by 4 percentage points since the December 
survey. 
  One-fourth, or 26 percent, of those interviewed said they 
were extremely dissatisfied. Another full one-fourth refused to 
state an opinion as to whether they were satisfied or 
dissatisfied. 
  The satisfaction of farmers with the government has risen by 
one-fifth since the previous poll. Of this occupational group, 
nearly half -- or 46 percent -- give the government a good 
grade. 
  Aho's own personal performance was also rated as 
satisfactory 
by around one-fifth of citizens. The prime minister's approval 
rating has risen by 4 points since December. 

</TEXT>

