<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Notes Success of Economic Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Notes Success of Economic Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1606111594 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1000 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1606111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Prime Minister Tansu Ciller has said that all the 
targets envisaged by the 5 April economic measures have been met 
so far and the rate of inflation has started to drop fast. 
  The prime minister visited the Turkish Union of Chambers and 
Stock Exchanges and met with Yalim Erez, the chairman of the 
Union, and other officials. 
  In a statement before the meeting, Prime Minister Ciller 
said 
a large portion of the work envisaged by the 5 April economic 
measures has been carried out. She pointed out that the 
measures received great support, both from international 
organizations and from the domestic public. The first positive 
results are being received, she said, adding that the mechanism 
is now at work that will seriously improve the exports that had 
reached a deadlock and the current transactions deficit that was 
getting larger and larger. 
  As a result of a series of measures that had to be taken, 
Ciller explained that, on the one hand, while the capital and 
interest on loans are being paid, one the other hand, getting 
further loans is being kept at a minimum. In this way, she 
said,the amount of money paid in interest from tax revenues has 
dropped significantly for the first time since 1987.. 
  The prime minister pointed out that the budget deficit, 
which 
had reached 32 trillion Turkish lira, was 4.5 trillion lira last 
month. This drop will continue, she stressed. 

</TEXT>

