<H3> <TI>   PP Leader Claims Poised Hammer Assisting PKK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PP Leader Claims Poised Hammer Assisting PKK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1506190794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1506190794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Prosperity Party [PP] leader Necmettin Erbakan has 
said that the Poised Hammer mandate has been extended, despite 
the fact that a majority of the people are against it. 
  Addressing the PP assembly group, Erbakan said the Poised 
Hammer forces are extending aid to the PKK [Workers Party of 
Kurdistan] terror organization and to Armenia. He noted that 
these forces are stationed in Turkey not to defend northern 
Iraqis but to watch over U.S. interests in the Middle East. 
  [Begin Erbakan recording] Some 70 to 80 percent of our 
citizens want these forces to leave Turkey. The administration 
is fulfilling the wishes of foreign forces, despite the will of 
the people and despite claims that there is democracy in Turkey. 
[end recording] 
  Commenting on the constitutional amendments, Erbakan said 
his 
party wants a laicism similar to that in Europe to be 
implemented in Turkey. Noting that constitutional amendments 
have been presented with the aim of covering up the 
deterioration in the economy, Erbakan added that the people 
want, above all, to be fed. 

</TEXT>

