<H3> <TI>   Kohl, Russia's Rybkin Meet in Bonn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl, Russia's Rybkin Meet in Bonn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606101494 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 0924 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606101494 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Chancellor Helmut Kohl praised the 
reconciliatory role of Moscow's State Duma Chairman Ivan Rybkin 
in Russian politics. According to government spokesman Dieter 
Vogel, during talks with Rybkin in Bonn Kohl also stressed 
Germany's "energetic interest" in the continuation of the 
democratic and market economic reform process in Russia on the 
basis of stable framework conditions. 
  The two politicians agreed "that bilateral relations are 
free 
from fundamental and insoluble problems." This positive 
starting point should be used and further developed in the 
interest of the two countries and all of Europe. The chairman 
of the Russian State Duma also plans to meet Bundestag President 
Rita Suessmuth and Federal President Richard von Weizsaecker 
today. 

</TEXT>

