<H3> <TI>   `Serious Installation Mistake' at Nuclear Station </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Serious Installation Mistake' at Nuclear Station </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606130394 Stockholm Sveriges Radio Network in Swedish 
1030 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606130394 </F>
<F P=104>  Stockholm Sveriges Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Swedish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A serious installation mistake has been discovered 
in the Forsmark nuclear power station during an overhaul, Radio 
Uppland reports. It is a so-called blast plate that has been 
installed incorrectly. The task of the blast plate is to 
explode if the pressure in the reactor becomes too high. 
Because the plate was incorrectly installed, it would not have 
been of any use if there had been an accident. According to Alf 
Lindfors, head of the Forsmark station, it is a serious matter 
that the fault was not discovered earlier. 

</TEXT>

