<H3> <TI>   UN's Efforts on Confidence-Building Measures Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN's Efforts on Confidence-Building Measures Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Outcome of Visit To Be Seen </H4>

<F P=102> NC1706114794 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1030 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1706114794 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Government Spokesman Ioannis Kasoulidhis said the 
outcome of Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis' meetings in the 
United States will be seen in the upcoming UN Security Council 
resolution. 
  The spokesman stressed that the foreign minister's mission 
was to present the Greek Cypriot side's positions, which were 
formed at the National Council. He added: At the same time, 
the goal of his mission was to persuade the UN Secretariat and 
the UN Security Council members of the correctness of the Greek 
Cypriot positions. 

