<H3> <TI>   12 Deputies Resign From Democracy Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    12 Deputies Resign From Democracy Party </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1506172294 Ankara ANATOLIA in Turkish 1440 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1506172294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  Turkish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara (AA) -- Twelve deputies from the Democracy 
Party [DEP] have resigned from their party. DEP acting leader 
Remzi Kartal sent a fax to the speaker of the Turkish Grand 
National Assembly [TGNA] informing him that the following 
deputies resigned from DEP: Hatip Dicle (Diyarbakir), Leyla 
Zana (Diyarbakir), Ahmet Turk (Mardin), Sirri Sakik (Mus), Orhan 
Dogan (Sirnak), Sedat Yurtdas (Diyarbakir), Selim Sadak 
(Sirnak), Ali Yigit (Mardin), Nizamettin Toguc (Batman), Mahmut 
Kilinc (Adiyaman), Naif Gunes (Siirt), Zubeyir Aydar (Siirt). 
  After the resignations, Remzi Kartal remains the only DEP 
deputy in the TGNA. 

</TEXT>

