<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cetin: Straits Regulations Not Discussed in London </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cetin: Straits Regulations Not Discussed in London </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1606161494 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1500 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1606161494 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Ankara, June 16 (A.A.) -- Foreign Minister Hikmet 
Cetin said on Thursday [16 June] that the regulations on the 
straits were under the authorization of Turkey and it will be 
put into effect on July 1 adding that giving up Turkey's 
sovereign rights was out of question. 
  Main opposition Motherland Party (ANAP) Deputy Bulent 
Akarcali, speaking in the parliament, claimed that decisions 
against Turkey's sovereign rights were made during a meeting of 
International Maritime Organization where Turkish delegation 
also attended in London last month. 
  Akarcali said all Turkish sovereign rights on the Bosporus 
and Dardanelles were transferred to international organizations. 
  He said Turkish delegation had no proposals while Greek 
proposals were approved of with the support of Russian, Greek 
and Greek- Cypriot representatives. 
  Answering the ANAP deputy's claims, Cetin said the stories 
taking place in the press were not based on facts. 
  Cetin said the straits regulations were not discussed during 
the so-called meeting adding that traffic schemes were brought 
to that meeting. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-43462 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drweu117_q_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-WEU-94-117 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  15 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Besharati Meets Turkish Parliament Speaker </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Besharati Meets Turkish Parliament Speaker </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506125994 Tehran IRNA in English 1231 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506125994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, June 15, IRNA -- Iranian Interior Minister 
'Ali Mohammad Besharati, now visiting Turkey, has said that the 
Islamic Republic of Iran is ready for promotion of ties with 
Turkey and for closer cooperation between parliaments of the two 
countries. 
  Besharati, who was speaking to the Turkish parliament 
speaker 
Tuesday [14 June], said the Ankara government should adopt a new 
strategy for its relations with its neighbors in view of the 
current changes sweeping the world. 
  He added that special conditions in Europe and elsewhere in 
the world call for strengthening of relations between the two 
neighboring countries of Iran and Turkey. 
  Besharati invited the Turkish parliament speaker to pay an 
official visit to Tehran. 
  The Turkish parliamentarian said that the parliament and 
nation of Turkey were satisfied with the existing "friendly" 
ties with the Islamic Republic of Iran. 
  He expressed hope that Irano-Turkish ties would further 
broaden in light of continued talks between the two countries' 
parliamentary officials. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

