<F P=100> TURKEY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Concludes `Fruitful' Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Concludes `Fruitful' Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506202894 Tehran IRNA in English 1551 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506202894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ankara, June 15, IRNA -- Iran's Interior Minister, 
'Ali Mohammad Besharati said at the end of his two day official 
visit to Turkey that he had had "very constructive and fruitful" 
talks with Turkish officials. 
  Talking to reporters at Ankara airport, Besharati and his 
Turkish counterpart Nahit Mentese expressed pleasure with the 
growing trend of Tehran-Ankara relations in all domains 
including cultural, social, diplomatic, economic, trade and 
security fields. 
  They called a protocol inked by two countries on expansion 
of 
border security cooperation one of the achievements of the 
two-day visit of the Iranian delegation to Turkey. 
  Besharati emphasized that Tehran and Ankara are concerned 
about the recent developments in northern Iraq, with both 
insisting on maintaining Iraq's territorial integrity. 
  Mentese said that during talks with Besharati both sides 
revised the provisions of letters of understanding signed 
earlier by Iran and Turkey, in addition to reaching agreement 
that the Iran-Turkey joint committee on security cooperation 
continue its activities. 
  During his two-day stay here, Besharati met with Turkish 
president Suleyman Demirel, Prime Minister Tansu Ciller and the 
ministers of foreign affairs and interior. 

</TEXT>

