<F P=102>   BR1706120094 Brussels BELGA Database in French 1422 GMT 16 
Jun 94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1706120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels BELGA Database </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article signed LAR/MJN: "Delcroix: Belgium Will Not Send </F>
Troops To Rwanda"] 
  [Text] Brussels, 16 June (BELGA) -- "If France decided to 
intervene in Rwanda within a multinational framework, Belgium 
would not send any troops," a spokesman for Defense Minister 
Delcroix stated on Thursday [16 June]. "It is not excluded that 
Belgium may provide logistic support, such as equipment, but the 
Belgian Government still has to decide on that on Friday," he 
stated. 
  Minister Delcroix believes that such an operation need not 
necessarily be carried out by the Blue Helmets, but it must 
nevertheless obtain UN backing. 

</TEXT>

