  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- FRG Chancellor Helmut Kohl has 
stressed Germany's vital interest in further reforms in Russia. 
On Thursday [16 June] during a meeting with Ivan Rybkin, 
chairman of the Russian State Duma, the chancellor paid tribute 
to his balancing role in Russian politics. According to 
Government Spokesman Dieter Vogel, both agreed that the 
relations between Bonn and Moscow are free from basic and 
unsolvable problems. 
  At the beginning of his four-day visit to Germany, Rybkin, 
who is close to the communist agriculture party in the State 
Duma, also met with President Richard von Weizsaecker and 
Bundestag President Rita Suessmuth. In addition, talks with 
Cabinet members and the chairmen of the Bundestag groups were 
scheduled. Rybkin wants to visit Cologne and Berlin over the 
weekend. 

