<H3> <TI>   Court Declares Instead Party Election Void </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Declares Instead Party Election Void </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1606195294 Hamburg DPA in German 1822 GMT 16 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1606195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Munich -- The election of Michael Bashford as the 
new federal chairman of the Instead Party was declared void by 
the Augsburg Land Court on Thursday [16 June]. The eighth 
chamber of the court says in its ruling that there were grave 
procedural mistakes in the 4 June election by the federal 
convention. This decision sustained the claim by Munich law 
professor Bernd Schuenemann, the previous chairman. 
  Under the threat of an administrative fine of up to 500,000 
German marks, Bashford and party founder Markus Wegner were 
forbidden to claim that Schuenemann was voted down by the 
federal convention. The claim that Bashford is the new federal 
chairman must not be made or spread either. 
  At the meeting in Hamburg, Bashford had won a majority. The 
court's ruling states that some of the land organizations had 
not been invited. Although the Hamburg Land Court had ruled 
prior to the convention that the North Rhine-Westphalian land 
organization must be invited, the North Rhine-Westphalian 
delegates had not had the right to vote, speak, or submit a 
motion. This is a clear violation of the delegates' rights, the 
ruling says. 

</TEXT>

