<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Martino Reassures Van Miert on </F>
Privatizations"] 
  [Text] (ANSA) Rome, June 16 -- Italy's privatizations will 
take place with full respect for European Union [EU] competition 
rules, Foreign Minister Antonio Martino reassured the EU 
commissioner for Competition, Karel van Miert, at a meeting here 
Thursday [16 June]. 
  A ministry communique said the meeting took place in a 
"cordial climate" and also covered a wide range of issues 
concerning European anti-trust and competition regulations, 
focussing on the new Rome government's "orientations" for 
privatizations. 
  Budget Minister Giancarlo Pagliarini also met Van Miert and 
discussed state aid to industry, privatizations, regional aid 
and tax rules for payments made by employers for pensions and 
welfare, a communique said. 
  Van Miert urged Rome to prepare as soon as possible a list 
of 
areas that may be eligible for EU funds. Most of the EU funds 
set aside for development and infrastructure projects in 
southern Italy over the past several years have not been used. 

