<H3> <TI>   Ministry Denies Involvment in Rwandan President's Death </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Denies Involvment in Rwandan President's Death </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706093294 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 0800 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706093294 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The French Foreign Ministry has denied the report in 
the 17 June issue of the Brussels daily LE SOIR, which hints 
that two members of the French armed forces were involved in the 
attack in which the president of Rwanda was killed. The French 
Foreign Ministry describes this as a ridiculous allegation, 
recalling that previous unfounded rumors have circulated 
implicating foreign countries. 
  In Kigali the Rwandan Patriotic Front [RPF], the rebel 
movement of the minority Tutsi ethnic group, has just seized 
control of the Sainte Famille Church. It was held by the 
government forces and Hutu militias until now. 

</TEXT>

