<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Suessmuth, Russia's Rybkin Urge More Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Suessmuth, Russia's Rybkin Urge More Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606162994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1545 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- Lower House President Rita 
Suessmuth and her Russian counterpart Ivan Rybkin have advocated 
greater cooperation between the two parliaments. Rybkin 
emphasized in Bonn today that the industrial-cultural exchanges 
are to be stepped up. The Russian parliamentary president, who 
had also met Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl and Federal 
President Richard von Weizsaecker, reviewed his talks 
positively. He emphasized: "We Russians and Germans cannot live 
without one another." 
  Kohl paid tribute to Rybkin's conciliatory role in Russian 
politics. At the same time, the chancellor underlined Germany's 
"vital interest" in the continuation of the democratic and 
economic reform process in Russia on the basis of stable 
framework conditions, government spokesman Dieter Vogel said. 
He also said that the politicians agreed "that bilateral 
relations are free of fundamental and insoluble problems." In 
the interest of the two countries and of the whole of Europe 
this positive starting position should be put to use and 
developed further. 

</TEXT>

