<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kohl Says Enemies of Freedom Must Be Opposed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kohl Says Enemies of Freedom Must Be Opposed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606153994 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1445 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606153994 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- On the occasion of the 41st 
anniversary of the popular uprising in the German Democratic 
Republic [GDR], Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl appealed to all 
German democrats "resolutely to oppose the enemies of freedom." 
Anyone playing down the Socialist Unity Party of Germany regime 
today was jeopardizing the "fundamental antitotalitarian 
consensus" in Germany, Kohl said in Bonn today. The same 
applied to those who sought to suppress the crimes of the 
national-socialist tyranny. Kohl added: "Left-wing and 
right-wing radicalism is shameful for our country." 
  The chancellor emphasized that remembering the popular 
uprising in the GDR of 17 June 1953 remained topical even after 
German unification. It united all democrats in the belief that 
there should never be another dictatorship. History has proved 
those right who at the time had "worked courageously and 
selflessly for freedom and German unity." Kohl recalled that 
the peaceful uprising in Berlin, Jena, and many other industrial 
centres of the former GDR was "brutally put down by the 
communist power apparatus." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

