<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   CSU Urges SPD To Dissociate From PDS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CSU Urges SPD To Dissociate From PDS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606133094 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1137 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Munich (DDP/ADN) -- Looking toward the anniversary 
of 17 June [1953 uprising in East Berlin], CSU [Christian Social 
Union] General Secretary Erwin Huber has called for a "decisive 
examination" of the "legacy of the SED [Socialist Unity Party of 
Germany] regime." If the successor party PDS [Party of 
Democratic Socialism] could get 25 percent of the votes in the 
local elections in the states of former East Germany, this is a 
serious danger for stability and internal peace in Germany, 
Huber said in Munich today. 
  Huber called on the SPD [Social Democratic Party] to clearly 
dissociate itself from the "SED-PDS." Any cooperation with this 
"left-wing extremist organization" has "to be taboo for a 
democratic party." The CSU will never let the "demons of 
dictatorship" again threaten the freedom of people in Germany. 

</TEXT>

