<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Peres in Vienna: `Israel's </F>
Relations With Austria Could Not Be Any Better!'"] 
  [Excerpt] Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres arrived in 
Vienna on an unofficial visit Tuesday [14 June]. The highlight 
of a short meeting with [Chancellor Franz] Vranitzky was Peres' 
statement: "We have no problems at all with Austria, relations 
could not be any better." It was not always like that, and it 
might become different with Italy. However, regarding questions 
in this connection Peres said that Prime Minister Berlusconi and 
Foreign Minister Martino were great friends of Israel. As far 
as the neofascist government members are concerned, one would 
have to wait and see. Peres appeared to be as optimistic as 
ever about the progress in the peace process, even though a 
severe controversy about Jerusalem flared up in the past few 
days. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

