<F P=102>   AU1906185594 Vienna KURIER in German 19 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1906185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna KURIER </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Liberal Selection"] </F>
  [Text] The Liberal Forum, which split off the Freedom Party 
of Austria 15 months ago, is girding itself for its first 
Nationalrat election campaign. In addition to Heide Schmidt, 
top candidate and leader of the federal list, the other four 
Liberal Forum deputies -- caucus Leader Frischenschlager, Thomas 
Barmueller, Hans Helmut Moser, and Vorarlberg deputy Klara 
Motter -- also plan to run. 
  Following Wolfgang Grassl's resignation, Hans Helmut Moser, 
federal manager ad interim, will take over heading the election 
campaign. 
  The provincial list and the list for the Vorarlberg Diet 
elections will be approved at the next federal congress on 18 
September. 

</TEXT>

