<H3> <TI>   Government Rejects Sending Soldiers to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Rejects Sending Soldiers to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806101394 Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International in 
English 0900 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1806101394 </F>
<F P=104>  Brussels Radio Vlaanderen International </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The Belgian Government has 
confirmed that our country will not send soldiers to Rwanda. 
According to Defense Minister Leo Delcroix, Belgium will, 
however, offer logistical support in the event of a military 
intervention. The Belgian Government has also earmarked 100 
million francs for humanitarian help for the Rwandans. It will 
be organized by four Belgian nongovernmental organizations. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

