<H3> <TI>   Cyprus' Foreign Minister Meets With Hurd in Oxford </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cyprus' Foreign Minister Meets With Hurd in Oxford </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1706165694 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1600 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1706165694 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Greek </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis met with 
British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd, with whom he discussed 
the latest developments in the Cyprus issue following UN 
Secretary General Butrus Butrus-Ghali's report. The meeting 
took place in Oxford, Hurd's electoral district, where the 
British foreign secretary was handling other business. 
  Speaking after the meeting, Mikhailidhis said that the two 
ministers exchanged views on the issue of the promotion of the 
confidence-building measures and on new developments following 
the latest Butrus-Ghali report. They also exchanged more 
general views on what the next steps should be. The foreign 
minister said he stressed that Cyprus will not participate in a 
dialogue to amend the 12 March document. Mikhailidhis also said 
that he briefed the British foreign secretary on the Cyprus 
Government's belief that there must be a new approach to the 
Cyprus issue. 
  Foreign Minister Mikhailidhis also said that during the 
meeting they discussed Cyprus' membership in the European Union 
[EU], as it will be considered during the upcoming EU Summit in 
Corfu. Mikhailidhis described his meeting with Hurd as very 
useful. The foreign minister will return to Cyprus this evening 
via Athens. 

</TEXT>

