<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    CDU Wins Communal Election in Saxony </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1706153094 Berlin DIE WELT in German 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1706153094 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DIE WELT </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [`DW' report: "CDU Remains Strongest Force in Saxony"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Although the Christian Democratic Union [CDU] 
was able to defend its position at the Saxony communal elections 
as the leading political force in Saxony, it received fewer 
votes at the municipal and district elections, as well as at the 
district and town council elections of cities that do not form 
part of districts, than in 1990. According to the preliminary 
result, the CDU received 38.1 percent of the votes, compared to 
44.6 percent in 1990. 
  The Social Democratic Party of Germany [SPD], Party of 
Democratic Socialism [PDS], and Alliance 90/Greens registered a 
clear increase in votes. The SPD received 21.6 percent of the 
vote (14.7 percent in 1990), the PDS 16.3 percent (11.6 percent 
in 1990), and Alliance 90/Greens 7.7 percent (4.5 percent in 
1990). The Free Democratic Party received 7.5 percent of the 
votes, compared to 6.3 percent in 1990, With 0.1 percent of the 
votes nationwide, the Republikaner suffered a clear political 
rebuff. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

