<H3> <TI>   Survey Shows Increased Support for Kohl </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Survey Shows Increased Support for Kohl </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1706140294 Hamburg BILD in German 17 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> AU1706140294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg BILD </F>
<F P=105>  German </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Survey"] </F>
  [Text] According to a survey by the Forsa Institute, Kohl 
enjoys increased support. Forty-one percent of respondents said 
they would vote for the chancellor (Christian Democratic Union) 
in an election, compared to 37 percent the previous week. 
Twenty-nine percent said they would vote for Scharping, the 
Social Democratic Party of Germany's [SPD] candidate, compared 
to 29 percent the previous week. For the first time, the 
coalition leads the SPD in the popularity table, with the 
support of 47 percent of respondents (Christian Democratic 
Union/Christian Social Union 42 percent and Free Democratic 
Party 5 percent). The SPD enjoyed the support of 36 percent of 
the respondents, Alliance 90/Greens 10 percent, Social 
Democratic Party [PDS] 4 percent, and Republikaner 2 percent. 
Last week, Alliance 90/Greens and Republikaner had the support 
of 3 and 2 percent of respondents respectively. 

</TEXT>

