<H3> <TI>   Socialist Party Leader Rocard Resigns </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Socialist Party Leader Rocard Resigns </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1906165394 Paris France-2 Teletext in French 1636 GMT 19 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1906165394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Teletext </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Michel Rocard resigned his post of first secretary 
of the Socialist Party on today. 
  The National Council of the Socialist Party issued a vote of 
no-confidence in Rocard, who had suggested broadening the 
leadership of the Socialist Party and "going beyond the 
ossification of factionalism." 
  The resolution put forward by Michel Rocard received 88 
votes 
in favor, 129 against, 48 abstentions, and two refusals to vote. 

</TEXT>

