<F P=103> LD1906201194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The Socialist Party this evening is looking for 
a new prodigy able to embody its ideas and to remotivate the 
electorate less than one year before the presidential elections. 
[passage omitted] The bitterness of Mr. Rocard and a strange 
day, as related by Ghislaine Chenu and Roland Sicard: 
  [Sicard] This is the first picture of Michel Rocard as a 
rank-and-file member of the Socialist Party. He has just been 
beaten, he is no longer the first secretary. His immediate 
reaction: 
  [Begin Rocard recording] This morning I suggested to the 
Socialist Party national council that it should go beyond 
factionalism. I suggested we should build a political movement 
which could meet the demands of the French people. Finally, I 
suggested that a team of gifted and sincere young politicians -- 
including Martine Aubry -- should join the national leadership. 
All this was rejected. This is why I resigned. It is now up 
to members to express themselves. As for me, I remain, I still 
am a fighter for hope. [end recording] [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

