<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Approves Military Programming Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senate Approves Military Programming Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR1606123694 Paris LE FIGARO in French 16 Jun 94 p 10 </F>
<F P=103> BR1606123694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris LE FIGARO </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Senate by a very large majority approved the 
1995-2000 Military Programming Law yesterday. Only the 
Communists voted against it. Since no amendment was retained, 
the law has now been definitively adopted. Answering questions 
with regard to the 2.5-billion-franc [Fr] freeze in the 
equipment budget (Fr1.9 billion) and the operating budget 
(Fr0.630 billion), Defense Minister Francois Leotard said that 
"France is engaged in a formidable economic war." Nevertheless, 
the defense minister hopes that this freeze will not lead to 
cancellation, as is feared by the Armed Forces, which saw their 
budget slashed already by Fr630 million in March. 

</TEXT>

