<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Previti Cautious on Sending Troops to Rwanda </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Previti Cautious on Sending Troops to Rwanda </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1906183194 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1745 
GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1906183194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Italian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Italy is the European country that has said most 
clearly that it is ready to intervene in Rwanda, but on 
condition that the intervention is not a unilateral or 
multilateral one, but it takes place under an international 
umbrella. Here is Defense Minister Cesare Previti: 
  [Begin Previti recording] We can take part in international 
humanitarian and peace operations. If we reach agreement to do 
something, we are ready and we have already said so. Reaching 
the agreement is the problem. We have tried to speed things up 
through the WEU [Western European Union]; there will be another 
meeting on Tuesday [21 June]. The French are insisting on a 
unilateral operation in which we have no intention of taking 
part, I believe. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

